l hours at −20 °C and form reversible, monophasic and clear gels. As the kV of these two binary mixtures is slightly above 6 mm2/s at 40 °C, they nearly meet the kV standard. Replacing ethanol by “ethanolotropes” like 2-MTHF or HepOH can lead to an increase of the monophasic region of these ternary mixtures at low temperatures. Moreover, this temperature dependence could be associated with the nanostructuring, since mixtures located in the bicontinuous-like regions seem to be more sensitive regarding their phase behaviour. © 2016
